The paper discusses the use of deep learning models for structured output prediction, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision research. The paper specifically focuses on image segmentation and multi-label classification, which are both subfields of computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning models for natural language processing tasks, which falls under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of deep learning models for security applications, which falls under the subfield of cryptography (cs.CR).
